cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI. 

This paper is about predicting issue lifetime in software development, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The authors use decision trees and correlation feature selection to achieve high precision and low false alarms, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.AI). They also address the problem of high class imbalance within issue datasets, which is a common issue in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, they mention using cross-project data to train their model, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or social and information networks (cs.SI) as they are leveraging data from multiple sources.
